11.name: Season 11
11.overview:
Strictly Come Dancing returned for its eleventh series beginning with a launch show on 7 September 2013, with the live shows starting on 27 and 28 September 2013. Sir Bruce Forsyth and Tess Daly continue to host, with Claudia Winkleman returning to host the results show alongside Daly. All four judges from the last series also returned.

The show will be broadcast from Blackpool Tower Ballroom on 16 November 2013.

episodes.name: Launch
episodes.overview:
Put your dancing shoes on, Strictly is back! It's glitz and glamour all the way as Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman launch the new series. Get on board the Strictly express as the journey begins for 15 new stars, including the nail-biting moment when they discover who their dancing partners are.

The couples then take to the dance floor to perform together for the very first time in their much-anticipated inaugural group routine. Will it be ballroom bliss or murder on the dance floor?

Plus, music performances from soul star Gregory Porter and singing sensation Jess Glynne.

episodes.name: Week 1 - Show 1
episodes.overview: Six of the couples take to the floor for the very first time.

episodes.name: Week 1 - Show 2
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the weekend's second live show.

episodes.name: Week 2
episodes.overview: All 15 couples hit the dance floor together for the first time.

episodes.name: Week 2 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the first results show of the series.

episodes.name: Week Three: Movie Special
episodes.overview: In this week's Movie Special, there is a pro group dance, and the remaining 14 couples perform a movie themed dance. Carol and Pasha find themselves bottom of the judges leader board with a score of just 17 for their South Pacific themed Quick Step. Jay and Aliona are top with a score of 37 (the best score and first '10' of the season) for their Pulp Fiction themed Jive.

episodes.name: Week Three Results
episodes.overview: There is a movie themed group dance plus music from Andrea Bocelli. Anthony and Oti, and Ainsley and Natalie find themselves in the bottom two and perform again in the dance off, with Anthony and Oti the second couple to leave the competition.

episodes.name: Week Four
episodes.overview: The remaining 13 couples perform for judges scores and audience votes. Jeremy and Karen find themselves bottom of the judges leader board with a score of 20 for their Jive, with Katie and Anton top with 33 for their American Smooth.

episodes.name: Week Four Results
episodes.overview: There is an 80's themed group dance plus music from guest Will Young. Daniel and Kristina, and Kirsty and Brendan find themselves in the bottom two and perform again in the dance off, with Daniel and Kristina leaving the competition.

episodes.name: Week Five
episodes.overview: The remaining 12 couples perform for judges scores and viewer votes. Helen and Aljaz, and Kellie and Kevin find themselves joint top of the judges leader board with scores of 35, with Ainsley and Natalie bottom with a score of 18 for their Waltz.

episodes.name: Week Five Results
episodes.overview: There is a group pro dance to The Sun Has Got His Hat On, and music from guest Bryan Adams. Jamelia and Tristan, and Ainsley and Natalie find themselves in the bottom two and have to dance again, with Ainsley and Natalie the latest to leave the competition.

episodes.name: Week Six: Halloween Special
episodes.overview: In a Halloween themed special there is a spooky group dance, and the remaining 11 couples perform for the judges. Georgia and Giovanni are top of the leader board with a score of 35 for their Ghostbusters themed Tango, with Carol and Pasha bottom with 13 for their Rumba.

episodes.name: Week Six Results
episodes.overview: In the Halloween Special results show there is a chess themed group pro dance plus music from James Morrison. Kirsty and Brendan, and Jamelia and Tristan find themselves in the bottom two and have to dance again, with Kirsty and Brendan becoming the latest couple to leave the competition.

episodes.name: Week Seven
episodes.overview: At the midway point of the competition, the final 10 couples perform. Peter and Janette find themselves at the top of the judges leader board with 38 points (the highest of the season) for their Charleston. Carol and Pasha are again bottom with just 17 for their American Smooth.

episodes.name: Week Seven Results
episodes.overview: There is a Remembrance Day special group Pro dance to In the Mood, plus music from Seal. In a shock, Kellie and Kevin (in his first ever dance off) find themselves in the bottom two, along with Carol and Pasha, with Carol and Pasha being voted out by the judges.

episodes.name: Week Eight
episodes.overview: The final 9 pairs dance it out for a place in next week's Blackpool special. Georgia and Giovanni are top of the judges leader board with a score of 39 points (the current highest of the season) for their Chicago based Charleston, with Jeremy and Karen bottom with 21 for their Quickstep.

episodes.name: Week Eight Results
episodes.overview: There is a group Pro dance to the music of Years & Years, plus music from other guest Brandon Flowers. Jamelia and Tristan again find themselves in the bottom two, along with Jeremy and Karen. Jeremy and Karen become the latest pair to be voted off the competition.

episodes.name: Week Nine: Blackpool Special
episodes.overview: In this season's Blackpool special there is a full group dance, and the remaining 8 couples take to the Tower Ballroom floor. For the first time Peter and Janette find themselves bottom of the judges leader board with a score of 29 for their Jive, with Georgia and Giovanni again top, with 38 for their American Smooth. Anita and Gleb, and Kellie and Kevin also both score their first '10s' of the season.

episodes.name: Week Nine Results
episodes.overview: In this week's results show from the Tower Ballroom, Blackpool, there is a group pro dance plus music from Anastacia and Take That. Jamelia and Tristan find themselves in the bottom two for the 5th time, along with Peter and Janette for their first. Both compete again in the dance off with Jamelia and Tristan controversially being voted off the show. For the first time this season the judges were split, with Len choosing to send Peter and Janette home.

episodes.name: Week Ten
episodes.overview: The final 7 couples perform their main dance, plus a 'Quickstepathon' for judges votes. Helen and Aljaz get the best main dance score, with 39 for their Viennese Waltz (their first '10s' of the season). After the 'Quickstepathon' (which Helen and Aljaz won), they remain top of the leader board with a score of 46, with Peter and Janette bottom with a score of 32.

episodes.name: Week Ten Results
episodes.overview: There is a laundrette themed pro group dance, plus music from guests Adam Lambert and Il Divo. Kellie and Kevin, and Peter and Janette find themselves in the bottom two and have to dance again, with Peter and Janette the latest to leave the competition.

episodes.name: The Quarter-Final: Musicals Special
episodes.overview: In this Musicals Special there is a group pro dance to That's Entertainment, and each of the remaining 6 couples perform a musicals based dance. Anita and Gleb find themselves bottom of the judges leader board with a score of 31 for their Argentine Tango to Cell Block Tango from Chicago. Top are Jay and Aliona for their Rumba from the musical Once.

episodes.name: The Quarter-Final Results
episodes.overview: There is a group pro dance with the West End cast of The Lion King, and music from guest Josh Groban. In another shock, Helen and Aljaz, and Georgia and Giovanni find themselves in the bottom two and dance again, with Helen and Aljaz being voted out of the competition.

episodes.name: The Semi-Final
episodes.overview: The final 5 couples perform two dances each for a chance to get through to the final. Kellie and Kevin receive the best judges score of the night (39 for their American Smooth), with Katie and Anton the lowest (just 25 for their Charleston). When both dance scores are added together, Kellie and Kevin are top of the leader board with 73/80, with Katie and Anton bottom with a combined score of 56/80.

episodes.name: The Semi-Final Results
episodes.overview: There is a group pro dance plus music from special guest Kylie Minogue. Katie and Anton, and Anita and Gleb find themselves in the bottom two and dance again, with Anita and Gleb just falling short of the Grand Final, and leaving the competition.

episodes.name: Week 2
episodes.overview:
All 15 couples hit the dance floor, together for the first time, in a dance floor spectacular. Every step counts as the judges' scores from last week are combined with those from this show. The celebrities are dancing for survival as the two lowest-scoring couples will face the dreaded dance-off in Sunday's Results Show.

The pressure is on. No-one wants to be the first to leave the competition.

episodes.name: Week 2 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman return as your hosts for an unforgettable evening of Strictly drama, in the first results show of the series. The judges' scores and public votes are in and the two couples with the lowest score dance off against each other, and one of them will chasse out of the competition for good. Plus our professional dancers will be treating us to a spectacular routine accompanying the legendary Barry Gibb.

episodes.name: Week 3 Results
episodes.overview: It is time for another couple to leave the show as movie weekend builds to its finale. The only sequel in Strictly is the dreaded dance-off, and no-one wants to find themselves in the bottom two. Plus Michael Ball and Alfie Boe perform a classic track from a Hollywood blockbuster.

episodes.name: Week 5
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman invite you to join them for another evening of glitter and glamour as the 11 remaining couples hit the dance floor for a ballroom battle to stay in the show. Voting lines will open at the end of the programme. Once the judges' scores have been added to viewer votes, the two lowest-scoring couples will perform again in the dance-off in the results show.

episodes.name: Week 5 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman welcome you to another exciting results show full of dance drama. The judges' scores and public votes have been combined, and the two couples with the lowest score will dance off against each other before 11 couples become 10. Including a performance from LeAnn Rimes. Who will survive another week, and who will be cha cha cha-ing off the dance floor?

episodes.name: Week 8 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the results of last night's viewers' vote, and reveal which couples are guaranteed a place in next week's show. The two lowest scoring pairs compete in a dance-off, before one of them leaves the contest. Plus, the professional dancers give a special performance for Remembrance Day and Andre Rieu gives his rendition of Hallelujah.

episodes.name: Week 9
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman invite viewers to join them for a memorable show at the historic Blackpool Tower Ballroom as the remaining seven celebrities battle it out on the world-famous dance floor. The show opens with a special Strictly performance from the professional dancers and celebrities, inspired by Fred Astaire and Ginger Rogers. Voting lines open at the end of the show. Once the judges' scores have been added to viewer votes, the two lowest-scoring couples will perform again in the dreaded dance-off in the results show.

episodes.name: Week 9 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman welcome viewers to another exciting results show from the world-famous Blackpool Tower Ballroom. The judges' scores and public votes have been combined, and the two couples with the lowest score dance off against each other, before seven couples become six. Featuring performances from pop superstar Rick Astley and Scottish rockers Simple Minds.

episodes.name: Week 10
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman invite viewers to join them for an evening of sequins and sparkles as the remaining couples hit the ballroom floor. The competition is at melting point as the six surviving couples dance not once, but twice, pivoting, twisting and turning to keep the glitterball trophy in their sights. After performing their routine, all six couples compete on the dance floor at the same time in the Cha Cha Challenge to earn valuable extra marks from the judges. Voting lines will open at the end of the show. Once the judges' scores have been added to viewer votes, the two lowest-scoring couples will perform again in the dreaded dance-off in the results show.

episodes.name: Week 10 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman welcome viewers to another exciting results show. The judges' scores and public votes have been combined, and the two couples with the lowest scores dance off against each other, before six couples become five. Pop songstress Ellie Goulding performs her new track Falling for You, and the professional dancers perform another amazing group routine.

episodes.name: Week 11
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman invite viewers to join them for an evening of sequins and sparkles as the remaining couples hit the ballroom floor. Voting lines will open at the end of the show. Once the judges' scores have been added to viewer votes, the two lowest-scoring couples will perform again in the dreaded dance-off in the results show.

episodes.name: Week 11 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman welcome viewers to another exciting results show. The judges' scores and public votes have been combined, and the two couples with the lowest scores dance off against each other, before one couple leaves the show.

episodes.name: Week 12
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman invite viewers to join them for the semi-final of Strictly Come Dancing. Fifteen couples have been whittled down to just four, with each couple having to perform two dances for a chance to win a place in the Strictly grand final. Voting lines will open at the end of the show. Once the judges' scores have been added to viewer votes, the two lowest-scoring couples will perform again in the dreaded dance-off in the results show.

episodes.name: Week 12 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman welcome viewers to the semi-final results show. The judges' scores and public votes have been combined, and the two couples with the lowest scores dance off against each other, before four couple become three. Featuring a routine by the professional dancers and a musical performance by Sting.

episodes.name: Week 10
episodes.overview: The seven remaining pro-celebrity duos return to the Elstree studio, in the wake of their expedition to the Lancashire coast last weekend for the annual Blackpool Tower special. The competition will be no less intense on coming back to familiar territory, though, as the celebrities and their seasoned dancing partners draw closer to the grand final. Judges Shirley Ballas, Bruno Tonioli, Darcey Bussell and Craig Revel Horwood are on hand to assess each pairing's skills as they perform their individual routines, before they all tackle the Paso Doble at the same time in a `Pasodoblathon'. As ever, though, the impressing the judges is only half of the battle, as the stars must also gain the approval of the viewing public, who are given a chance to have their say over who should stay in the running.

episodes.name: Launch
episodes.overview: Strictly is back with a new line-up of celebrities and a new judge, Motsi, joining Craig, Bruno and Shirley. Kylie Minogue, Mark Ronson and Yebba perform in the studio.

episodes.name: Week 1
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the first live episode of the year. The 15 couples perform, hoping to impress judges Motsi Mabuse, Bruno Tonioli, Craig Revel Horwood and Shirley Ballas.

episodes.name: Week 2
episodes.overview: Our fifteen couples return to the ballroom for what promises to be a sensational night of dance.

episodes.name: Week 2 - Results
episodes.overview: The first results show of the series opens with a spectacular flamenco-inspired group performance from the pros, and there’s music from the amazing Lewis Capaldi.

episodes.name: Week 3 - Movie Week
episodes.overview: Tonight the glitz and glamour of Hollywood comes to the Strictly ballroom for a movie special. The show stars with an epic group routine before our remaining cast of 14 perform to some the most iconic movie songs of all time. Who will be a box office smash and who will end up on the cutting room floor?

episodes.name: Week 3 - Results
episodes.overview: Tonight, this week's movie special reaches its thrilling climax. The show starts with a blockbuster group routine from our stellar cast before the remaining 14 Strictly stars find out who must face the drama of the Dance Off. There’s also music from Harry Connick Jr, who will be performing Anything Goes.

episodes.name: Launch Show
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman host the launch of the 20th series, joined by judges Shirley Ballas, Anton Du Beke, Craig Revel Horwood and Motsi Mabuse as they welcome 15 new celebrities to the Strictly ballroom. Featuring a guest appearance by John Legend, and last year's champions Rose Ayling-Ellis and Giovanni Pernice reprising their winning routine

episodes.name: Week 1
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman host the first live show of the series. Judges Craig Revel Horwood, Motsi Mabuse, Anton Du Beke and Shirley Ballas assess the routines of the 15 couples, with the scores they award tonight being carried over to next week when viewers will have their chance to vote. Plus, a special group routine from the professional dancers

episodes.name: Week 2
episodes.overview: Our 15 new couples return to the Strictly ballroom. They’ve broken in their dancing shoes and are now performing live to keep their place in the competition. This week, not only do they have to impress the judges but also the viewers at home, as for the first time this series, the public vote will open.

episodes.name: Week 2 Results
episodes.overview: Two couples face the first dance-off of the series. Entertaining us all in the ballroom is the legendary Robbie Williams.

episodes.name: Week 3 Movie Week
episodes.overview: It's time to roll out the red carpet as Strictly Come Dancing takes you to the movies. Our remaining couples' routines take their inspiration from the silver screen.

episodes.name: Week 3 Results
episodes.overview: Two couples face a Movie Week dance-off. With a guest performance by Adam Lambert.

episodes.name: Week 4 Results
episodes.overview: The results show opens with a routine from our professional dancers and George Ezra performing in the Strictly Ballroom. One couple's fate hangs in the balance as your votes at home decide who will be in the bottom two and who has to fight for their place in the competition. Who will stay and who will go through to the BBC100 Special next week? Find out tonight

episodes.name: Week 5 Celebrating BBC 100
episodes.overview: To celebrate 100 years of the BBC, the couples dance to iconic BBC theme tunes.

episodes.name: Week 6 Halloween Special
episodes.overview: It's the Strictly Come Dancing Halloween special! Our remaining couples perform fierce and fun routines for all the family to enjoy.

episodes.name: Week 6 Results
episodes.overview: Another two couples face a dance-off, and there's a music performance by the outstanding Rina Sawayama. Who will the judges trick and treat this Halloween?

episodes.name: Week 7 Results
episodes.overview: Two more couples face a dance-off, and there is a music performance by Luke Evans.

episodes.name: Week 8
episodes.overview: The couples fight to secure a place in next week's Blackpool special.

episodes.name: Week 8 Results
episodes.overview: Two more couples face a dance-off, our professionals mark Remembrance Sunday with a beautiful group number, and the guest music performance is by Sheku and Zak.

episodes.name: Week 9 Blackpool
episodes.overview: After a two-year absence, Strictly Come Dancing returns to the iconic Blackpool Tower Ballroom.

episodes.name: Week 9 Results
episodes.overview: Two more couples face a dance-off, and Sam Ryder performs in the ballroom. At this stage of the competition, no-one wants to go home. Who will the judges save for another week?

episodes.name: Week 10
episodes.overview: The couples have to do more than ever to secure their places in next week's Musicals Special quarter-final.

episodes.name: Week 10 Results
episodes.overview: Two more couples face a dance-off, and special guests Tom Grennan and Joel Corry perform in the ballroom.

episodes.name: Week 11 Musicals
episodes.overview: The show makes a rare second appearance this week as the quarter-final is moved forward a day thanks to World Cup coverage. This musicals-themed edition opens with a dance extravaganza performed by the professional dancers alongside West End legends Marisha Wallace, Ivano Turco and Trevor Dion Nicholas. Fleur, Hamza, Helen, Kym, Molly and Will then take to the ballroom floor with routines inspired by the world of musical theatre. Everyone wants to secure their place in next week's semi-final, so showstopping performances and a stellar night of dance are to be expected.

episodes.name: Week 11 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present as the two lowest-scoring couples compete in the dance-off, with a place in the semi-final up for grabs. There's also a performance from the cast of The Cher Show and a Guys and Dolls routine from the professionals

episodes.name: Week 12 Semi-Final
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman present the semi-final of the pro-celebrity contest, for which Fleur, Hamza, Helen, Molly and Will must master two brand new routines to win the approval of judges and viewers alike and secure a place in next week's grand final

episodes.name: Week 12 Results
episodes.overview: Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman announce the results of the judges' scores and viewers' votes, with the two couples with the lowest combined scores taking part in a dance-off to decide who will be next to leave the contest and who will win the last place in next week's final. Craig Revel Horwood joins the professionals for a special routine, and there is music from Lewis Capaldi

episodes.name: Week 13 Final
episodes.overview: The final 4, Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman introduce the climax of this year's series.

episodes.name: Launch Show
episodes.overview: Strictly Come Dancing is back! Join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman as 15 brand new celebrities are welcomed to the Strictly ballroom.

episodes.name: Week 1
episodes.overview: Tess and Claud are back with the first live show of Strictly Come Dancing 2023, opening with a stunning group performance from our professional dancers showing the brand new cast how it’s done

episodes.name: Week 2
episodes.overview: The 15 new couples return live to the Strictly ballroom and perform to keep their place in the competition. The week one leaderboard stands as the judges scores have been carried over from last week, and at the end of the show, the public vote will open for the first time this series

episodes.name: Week 2 Results
episodes.overview: It’s the first results show of the series, and it opens with an incredible group number medley in tribute to the iconic Tina Turner.

episodes.name: Week 3
episodes.overview: The magic of the movies comes to the Strictly ballroom as the show opens with a beautiful routine by our professional dancers celebrating 100 years of Disney. Taking inspiration from movie blockbusters, iconic animations and timeless classics, our couples are all hoping to impress the judges and audiences at home ahead of the second results show of the series.

episodes.name: Week 3 Results
episodes.overview: Movie Week continues. Opening the results show, our professional dancers take us on a visit to Barbie Land, and the incredible Madison Beer performs in the ballroom. Two couples will face each other in the Movie Week dance-off. Who will the judges save, and who will leave the competition this weekend?

episodes.name: Week 4
episodes.overview: It’s week four of the competition, and our remaining couples are back on the ballroom floor, dancing for your votes at home. Hoping to impress the judges and land in an enviable position on the leader board is only half the story. Your votes will decide the bottom two for Sunday night’s results show.

episodes.name: Week 4 Results
episodes.overview:
The results show opens with a beautiful love story from our professional dancers, and the incredible Beverley Knight performs in the ballroom.

Our couples' fate hangs in the balance, as your votes at home decide who will be in the bottom two. Which two couples will be fighting for their place in the competition? All will be revealed on Sunday evening.

episodes.name: Week 5
episodes.overview: Join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman live from the Strictly Ballroom as our remaining couples take to the floor with more brand new, spectacular routines. With a place at next week’s Halloween Special up for grabs, expect our celebrities to pull out all the stops to impress both the judges and you at home.

episodes.name: Week 5 Results
episodes.overview: Tonight’s results show opens with a 60s Fosse-inspired number from our Strictly professionals and a music performance from Bastille. Sadly, one couple’s time on Strictly will come to an end as the two couples with the lowest combined judges' score and viewer vote will face each other in the dance-off. Who will the judges save and who will leave the competition?

episodes.name: Halloween Special
episodes.overview: It’s the Strictly Come Dancing Halloween Special! The remaining couples will perform lots of tricks and treats to wow the judges and win your votes at home. We are fast approaching the halfway point in the competition, and no-one wants to go home. Who will top the Halloween leaderboard?

episodes.name: Week 6 Results
episodes.overview: The results show opens with a Wednesday Addams-inspired routine from the Strictly professionals, and there will be a music performance from the legend that is Rick Astley. The two couples with the lowest combined judges score and viewer vote will have to face each other in the dance-off. Only one couple will return to dance again.

episodes.name: Week 7
episodes.overview: Halfway through the series, the competition is still wide open. The couples are back with their brand new routines, hoping to impress the judges and you at home. Join Tess and Claudia for another weekend of spectacular dancing.

episodes.name: Week 7 Results
episodes.overview:
Everyone is back in the ballroom for the Week 7 results show, opening with a magnificent Afro-Latin festival routine from our Strictly professionals alongside some special guests and a performance from Swedish pop singer Zara Larsson.

The two couples with the lowest combined judges score and viewer votes will face each other in the dance-off. Sadly, another couple will leave the competition.

episodes.name: Week 8
episodes.overview: Join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman as the remaining couples bring more fantastic routines to the Strictly ballroom. It's an important week to impress the judges and win votes at home as the couples are fighting for a place in next week's Blackpool special.

episodes.name: Week 8 Results
episodes.overview: The results show opens with a beautiful Remembrance Sunday routine from the professional dancers and a very special music performance from Andrea and Virginia Bocelli. The two couples with the lowest combined judges score and viewer vote will have to face each other in the dance-off. Who will they take through to Blackpool and who will leave the competition?

episodes.name: Blackpool Special
episodes.overview:
The time has arrived for the Strictly Blackpool Special, live from the iconic Blackpool Tower Ballroom. We celebrate our annual trip to the home of ballroom dancing with an incredible opening routine from our Strictly cast, before our remaining couples take to the most famous sprung floor in the country and pull out all the stops with some spectacular routines.

Who will steal the show? Join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman alongside our judges for the highly anticipated Blackpool Special.

episodes.name: Blackpool Special Results
episodes.overview: It’s back to the Blackpool Tower for the results show. Our professional dancers open the show with a fantastic group number, and Madness perform in the ballroom. At this stage of the competition, no-one wants to go home. Who will the judges save for another week?

episodes.name: Week 10
episodes.overview: As Strictly Come Dancing approaches the business end of the competition, the couples have more to do than ever to secure their place in the quarter-final Musicals Special. Expectations are high for the judges, so join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman for another weekend of fantastic ballroom dancing.

episodes.name: Week 10 Results
episodes.overview: The show opens with a Hollywood glam-inspired routine from our professional dancers, with Texas performing in the ballroom. Our couples can do no more. How have your votes at home changed the leaderboard? With a place in the Musicals Special quarter-final up for grabs, the dance-off is not to be missed. Who will the judges save, and who will be your 2023 quarter-finalists?

episodes.name: Musicals Special
episodes.overview:
The week of the musicals special has arrived, and it opens with a beautiful My Fair Lady group number from our professional dancers. Our remaining couples will take to the ballroom floor, with more incredible routines inspired by the world of musical theatre.

Who will steal the limelight? Everyone wants to secure their place in next week’s semi-final, so expect showstopping performances and a magical night of dance.

episodes.name: Week 11 Results
episodes.overview:
This week's results show opens with our professional dancers performing a dazzling routine inspired by Chorus Line, and also features music from Joss Stone singing This Time from the brand new musical The Time Traveller's Wife.

Will your votes at home change the musicals week leaderboard? The two couples with the lowest combined score will face each other in the dance-off. Which of our couples will be your 2023 semi-finalists?

episodes.name: Week 12
episodes.overview: It's the semi-final, with our couples performing twice in their bid to make it through to the grand final. It will be the most challenging week yet for our celebrities as they master two brand new routines, hoping to wow the judges and win your votes at home. The Glitterball Trophy is within touching distance for our remaining couples. No-one wants to lose their spot in next week’s final.

episodes.name: Week 12 Results
episodes.overview: The final results show of 2023 opens with a fantastic group number from our Strictly professionals and an incredible music performance from Take That. Your votes at home have never been more important as you are choosing your Strictly Come Dancing 2023 finalists. The two couples with the lowest overall points will go head-to-head in the last dance-off of the series.

episodes.name: The Final
episodes.overview:
It’s the grand final of Strictly Come Dancing 2023. After 12 weeks of competition, we have our finalists, and one of them will lift the Glitterball Trophy tonight. Join Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman as our remaining couples perform three incredible routines in a bid to be your Strictly Champion.

Cher will be performing and the cast of 2023 will return for one more epic routine. In the final, the judges’ scores are for guidance only the winner lies entirely in your hands.

Who will you crown Strictly Come Dancing Champion 2023?
